    "130687": {
      "id": 130687,
      "title": {
        "english": "Alya Sometimes Hides Her Feelings in Russian",
        "romaji": "Tokidoki Bosotto Russiago de Dereru Tonari no Alya-san",
        "native": "時々ボソッとロシア語でデレる隣のアーリャさん"
      },
      "synonyms": [
        "Roshidere",
        "The Neighboring Aarya-san who Sometimes Acts Affectionate and Murmuring in Russian",
        "Alya, Who Sits Next to Me, Sometimes Whispers Sweet Nothings in Russian",
        "คุณอาเรียโต๊ะข้างๆ พูดรัสเซียหวานใส่ซะหัวใจจะวาย",
        "Arya bàn bên thỉnh thoảng lại trêu ghẹo tôi bằng tiếng Nga",
        "Tokidoki Bosotto Russiago de Dereru Tonari no Aarya-san",
        "ロシデレ",
        "Alya flüstert mir auf Russisch süße Worte zu",
        "不時輕聲地以俄語遮羞的鄰座艾莉同學",
        "가끔씩 툭하고 러시아어로 부끄러워하는 옆자리의 아랴 양"
      ],
      "description": "Alisa Mikhailovna Kujou is Seiren Private Academy’s “solitary princess.” She’s a half-Russian beauty with silver hair, at the top of her class, student council accountant, and…completely unapproachable. For some reason, she’s also taken on the responsibility of reprimanding the slacker who sits next to her in class. Masachika Kuze is constantly frustrating her by falling asleep, forgetting his textbooks, and just being an overall unexemplary student. Or at least, that’s how it looks from the outside. She may put on a tough act, but she doesn’t mind Masachika as much as others would think. She even lets him call her by her nickname, Alya. Anyone hearing the comments she mutters in Russian under her breath might know how she really feels, but since none of her classmates understand the language, she’s free to say whatever she likes! Except…there is one person who knows what she’s saying. Masachika eavesdrops on her embarrassing revelations, pretending to be clueless, all the while wondering what her flirtatious comments actually mean!\n<br><br>\n(Source: Yen Press)\n<br><br>\n<i>Note: This entry includes volume 4.5.</i>",
      "status": "RELEASING",
