  "home": {
    "trending": [
      {
        "id": 105778,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Chainsaw Man",
          "english": "Chainsaw Man"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "extraLarge": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx105778-euxXZEIfDY2u.png",
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx105778-euxXZEIfDY2u.png"
        },
        "bannerImage": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/105778-xpU0zxrlU2Ux.jpg",
        "description": "The name says it all! Denji's life of poverty is changed forever when he merges with his pet chainsaw dog, Pochita! Now he's living in the big city and an official Devil Hunter. But he's got a lot to learn about his new job and chainsaw powers!<br>\n<br>\n(Source: MANGA Plus)<br>\n<br>\n<i>Notes:<br>\n- Nominated for the 2020 Manga Taisho Award.<br>\n- Winner of the 2021 Kono Manga ga Sugoi Award.<br>\n- Winner of the 66th Shogakukan Manga Award in the shounen category.<br>\n- Winner of the 2021 and 2022 Harvey Award for Best Manga.<br>\n- Chapters 1-97 were released in Weekly Shounen Jump from Dec 3, 2018 to Dec 13, 2020. The series resumed from Ch. 98 in Shounen Jump+ on July 12, 2022</i>",
        "genres": [
          "Action",
          "Comedy",
          "Drama",
          "Horror",
          "Supernatural"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 170400,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Byeoreul Pumeun Swordmaster",
          "english": "The Stellar Swordmaster"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "extraLarge": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx170400-yMIuOIboWuoO.jpg",
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx170400-yMIuOIboWuoO.jpg"
        },
        "bannerImage": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/170400-EgLAQtqhdQAx.jpg",
        "description": "The so-called “Lighthouse of the North,” the prosperous trading town of Schoarra, hides a dark underbelly: seedy slums ruled by five ruthless crime bosses. When streetwise orphan Vlad finds the brothel he works for decimated by a disgraced knight, he turns to the path of the blade, pledging himself to the pursuit of power by sword. Blessed with the ability to seek wisdom from his sentient sword, Vlad embarks upon a journey of growth and peril as swordsman in service to the powerful House Vayezid.<br>\n<br>\n(Source: WEBTOON)",
        "genres": [
          "Action",
          "Adventure",
          "Fantasy"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 119257,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Jeonjijeok Dokja Sijeom",
          "english": "Omniscient Reader"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "extraLarge": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx119257-Pi21aq3ey9GG.jpg",
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx119257-Pi21aq3ey9GG.jpg"
        },
        "bannerImage": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/119257-RtxJMRCunHXc.jpg",
        "description": "Back then, Dok-Ja had no idea. He had no idea his favorite web novel 'Three Ways to Survive the Apocalypse' was going to come to life, and that he would become the only person to know how the world was going to end. He also had no idea he would end up becoming the protagonist of this novel-turned-reality. Now, Dok-Ja will go on a journey to change the course of the story and save humankind once and for all.\n<br><br>\n(Source: WEBTOON, edited)",
        "genres": [
          "Action",
          "Adventure",
          "Fantasy"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 159930,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Muhanui Mabeopsa",
          "english": "The Infinite Mage"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "extraLarge": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx159930-qK1P4BNQL0zG.jpg",
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx159930-qK1P4BNQL0zG.jpg"
        },
        "bannerImage": null,
        "description": "After Sirone was abandoned in a stable, he was found by a family of hunters and raised in a loving home. Despite the hardships of the peasant life, he learned how to read from a young age and became obsessed with books, especially ones on the history of magic. One day, he has an unlikely encounter with a mage and learns how to enter the \"spirit zone,\" the first step to learning how to use magic. Although they say only nobles can be mages, will Sirone be able to prove his infinite potential?\n<br><br>\n(Source: Tapas)",
        "genres": [
          "Action",
          "Adventure",
          "Drama",
          "Fantasy"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 144946,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Gachiakuta",
          "english": "Gachiakuta"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "extraLarge": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx144946-cscic3n2SwdY.jpg",
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx144946-cscic3n2SwdY.jpg"
        },
        "bannerImage": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/144946-85c80rNqlAPp.jpg",
        "description": "A boy lives in a floating town, where the poor scrape by and the rich live a sumptuous life, simply casting their garbage off the side, into the abyss. When he’s falsely accused of murder, though, his wrongful conviction leads to an unimaginable punishment—exile off the edge, with the rest of the trash. Down on the surface, the cast-off waste of humanity has bred vicious monsters, and to travel the path to vengeance against those who cast him into Hell, a boy will have to become a warrior…\n<br><br>\n(Source: Kodansha USA)",
        "genres": [
          "Action",
          "Drama",
          "Fantasy"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 30013,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "ONE PIECE",
          "english": "One Piece"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "extraLarge": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx30013-BeslEMqiPhlk.jpg",
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx30013-BeslEMqiPhlk.jpg"
        },
        "bannerImage": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/30013-hbbRZqC5MjYh.jpg",
        "description": "As a child, Monkey D. Luffy was inspired to become a pirate by listening to the tales of the buccaneer \"Red-Haired\" Shanks. But his life changed when Luffy accidentally ate the Gum-Gum Devil Fruit and gained the power to stretch like rubber...at the cost of never being able to swim again! Years later, still vowing to become the king of the pirates, Luffy sets out on his adventure...one guy alone in a rowboat, in search of the legendary \"One Piece,\" said to be the greatest treasure in the world...\n<br><br>\n(Source: VIZ Media)",
        "genres": [
          "Action",
          "Adventure",
          "Comedy",
          "Fantasy"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 106929,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Eleceed",
          "english": "Eleceed"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "extraLarge": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx106929-flAUvHZDUz5v.jpg",
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx106929-flAUvHZDUz5v.jpg"
        },
        "bannerImage": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/106929-jYmT1n3Z0m46.jpg",
        "description": "Jiwoo is a kind-hearted young man who harnesses the lightning quick reflexes of a cat to secretly make the world a better place – one saved little child or foster pet at a time. Kayden is a secret agent on the run, who finds himself stuck in the body of a…um…decidedly fat old fluffy cat. Together, armed with Jiwoo’s super powers and Kayden’s uber-smarts, they’re out to fight those forces who would let evil rule this world. That is, if they can stand each other long enough to get the job done.\n<br><br>(Source: WEBTOONS)",
        "genres": [
          "Action",
          "Comedy",
          "Supernatural"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 180890,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Cheonhajeirinui Sokkupchingu",
          "english": "Shadow of the Supreme"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "extraLarge": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx180890-GRVR4m4ImzQN.jpg",
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx180890-GRVR4m4ImzQN.jpg"
        },
        "bannerImage": null,
        "description": "Yang-Cheon Ku, born to the virtuous House of Ku of Sanseo, the Little Star and next Head of House. Status: The world’s most hated demonic martial artist. Cause of death: Defeated during the Virtuous-Demonic War, tortured upon capture. Or so he thought. Moments after dying in the arms of his childhood friend, the Heavenly Sword herself, Seol-ah Wi, he finds himself back in the past. Already things have changed, but is it enough to ensure his second chance at life doesn’t end with the same regrets?\n<br><br>\n(Source: Tapas)",
        "genres": [
          "Action",
          "Adventure",
          "Fantasy"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 169904,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Ogami Tsumiki to Kinichijou.",
          "english": "Tsumiki Ogami's Not-So-Ordinary Life"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "extraLarge": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx169904-6gvkXMNpq66N.jpg",
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx169904-6gvkXMNpq66N.jpg"
        },
        "bannerImage": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/169904-DKM09rVWS7g0.jpg",
        "description": "Yutaka Shinso is constantly worried about what other people think of him. Hoping to turn over a new leaf, he changes high schools, but there’s something strange afoot: vampires, ogres, and all manner of supernatural beings walk the halls! Yutaka is particularly drawn to Tsumiki Ogami, a confident and popular werewolf. Will Tsumiki be the one to help Yutaka overcome his insecurities?\n<br><br>\n(Source: VIZ Media)\n<br><br>\n<i>Note:<br>\n- Placed third in the Tsugimanga 2024 Award in the Print Manga Category.</i>",
        "genres": [
          "Comedy",
          "Romance",
          "Supernatural"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 180422,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Momose Akira no Hatsukoi Hatan-chuu.",
          "english": "Akira Failing in Love"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "extraLarge": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx180422-dRRQ8aeSAYum.jpg",
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx180422-dRRQ8aeSAYum.jpg"
        },
        "bannerImage": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/180422-Ioj3Znc9FvrQ.jpg",
        "description": "Akira returns to the countryside for high school with a plan to win the heart of her childhood crush! They're both fools in love… because she's too dense to figure out he likes her back!<br><br>(Source: VIZ Media)",
        "genres": [
          "Comedy",
          "Romance"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 152913,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Anta to Osananajimitte dake demo Iyananoni!: Zekkou kara Hajimaru S-kyuu Bishoujo to no Gakuen Nariagari Seikatsu",
          "english": null
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "extraLarge": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/b152913-5EzfZeXchiSO.jpg",
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/b152913-5EzfZeXchiSO.jpg"
        },
        "bannerImage": null,
        "description": "Kazuma Suzuki was just your average high schooler—until his childhood friend, Rua Takayashiki, a beautiful, sharp-tongued girl who also happened to be the granddaughter of the school chairman and the nation’s top idol, cut all ties with him using a line straight out of a drama.\n<br><br>\nForced into submission for years as her so-called childhood friend, Kazuma decides it’s finally time for his first-ever rebellion. He’s done playing lapdog. This time, he’s taking back his freedom—and aiming for a normal school life.\n<br><br>\nEscaping a powerful beauty like her is easier said than done...\n<br><br>\n(Source: Square Enix)",
        "genres": [
          "Comedy",
          "Romance"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 169272,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Mayonaka Heart Tune",
          "english": "Tune In to the Midnight Heart"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "extraLarge": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx169272-1a2RZ43tqOdw.jpg",
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx169272-1a2RZ43tqOdw.jpg"
        },
        "bannerImage": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/169272-2LF1bU4MnwQc.jpg",
        "description": "When Arisu Yamabuki was all alone in bed at night, he was able to find solace in the voice of a radio host who went by “Apollo.” However, one day, she simply stopped broadcasting without any explanation. Years then passed, and Arisu is now a second-year high-schooler. He makes it his mission to search for Apollo, as there is something he wants to tell her. He doesn’t know what she looks like, or even what her real name is, but he manages to get some leads on her in his school’s broadcasting club. That’s where he meets four girls who all dream to get a job where they can make full use of their voices! Just who is Apollo, and how will those four’s dreams pan out?\n<br><br>\n(Source: K MANGA)",
        "genres": [
          "Comedy",
          "Romance"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 122063,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Shangri-La Frontier: Kusoge Hunter, Kami ge ni Idoman to su",
          "english": "Shangri-La Frontier"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "extraLarge": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx122063-j2wIvwb6yzPM.jpg",
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx122063-j2wIvwb6yzPM.jpg"
        },
        "bannerImage": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/122063-af2r0eldq5qc.jpg",
        "description": "Second year high school student Rakuro Hizutome is interested in one thing only: finding \"shitty games\" and beating the crap out of them. His gaming skills are second to none, and no game is too bad for him to enjoy. So when he's introduced to the new VR game Shangri-La Frontier, he does what he does best—min-maxes and skips the prologue to jump straight into the action. But can even an expert gamer like Rakuro discover all the secrets that Shangri-La Frontier hides...?\n<br><br>\n(Source: Kodansha USA)\n<br/>",
        "genres": [
          "Action",
          "Adventure",
          "Comedy",
          "Fantasy",
          "Sci-Fi"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 152404,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Tokidoki Bosotto Russiago de Dereru Tonari no Alya-san",
          "english": "Alya Sometimes Hides Her Feelings in Russian"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "extraLarge": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/b152404-PeFLFZXXuVr2.jpg",
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/b152404-PeFLFZXXuVr2.jpg"
        },
        "bannerImage": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/152404-MlAq7ISNxBfP.jpg",
        "description": "Masachika Kuse sits next to Alya, a girl of Russian and Japanese descent. She's beautiful, haughty, and an exceptional student, while Masachika is nerdy and known for being a slacker. He's an easy target for her comments in Russian, which she's all too happy to translate—except he can understand what she's really saying!\n<br><br>\n(Source: K Manga)",
        "genres": [
          "Comedy",
          "Romance"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 99943,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Kanojo, Okarishimasu",
          "english": "Rent-A-Girlfriend"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "extraLarge": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/large/bx99943-DX7nDMeqSTk3.png",
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx99943-DX7nDMeqSTk3.png"
        },
        "bannerImage": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/banner/99943-bs6PEAZgj1wy.jpg",
        "description": "In today’s Japan, “rental” services can deliver an afternoon with a “friend,” a “parent,” even a fake girlfriend! After a staggering betrayal by his girlfriend, hapless freshman Kazuya gets just desperate enough to give it a try. But he quickly discovers how complicated it can be to “rent” an emotional connection, and his new “girlfriend,” who’s trying to keep her side hustle secret, will panic when she finds out her real life and Kazuya’s are intertwined in surprising ways! Family, school, and life all start to go wrong, too… It’s sweet but naïve boy meets cute but ruthless girl in this 21st-century manga rom-com!\n<br><br>\n(Source: Kodansha USA)",
        "genres": [
          "Comedy",
          "Drama",
          "Ecchi",
          "Romance"
        ]
      }
    ],
    "popular": [
      {
        "id": 105778,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Chainsaw Man",
          "english": "Chainsaw Man"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx105778-euxXZEIfDY2u.png"
        },
        "description": "The name says it all! Denji's life of poverty is changed forever when he merges with his pet chainsaw dog, Pochita! Now he's living in the big city and an official Devil Hunter. But he's got a lot to learn about his new job and chainsaw powers!<br>\n<br>\n(Source: MANGA Plus)<br>\n<br>\n<i>Notes:<br>\n- Nominated for the 2020 Manga Taisho Award.<br>\n- Winner of the 2021 Kono Manga ga Sugoi Award.<br>\n- Winner of the 66th Shogakukan Manga Award in the shounen category.<br>\n- Winner of the 2021 and 2022 Harvey Award for Best Manga.<br>\n- Chapters 1-97 were released in Weekly Shounen Jump from Dec 3, 2018 to Dec 13, 2020. The series resumed from Ch. 98 in Shounen Jump+ on July 12, 2022</i>",
        "genres": [
          "Action",
          "Comedy",
          "Drama",
          "Horror",
          "Supernatural"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 105398,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Na Honjaman Level Up",
          "english": "Solo Leveling"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx105398-b673Vt5ZSuz3.jpg"
        },
        "description": "In a world where awakened beings called “Hunters” must battle deadly monsters to protect humanity, Seong Jin-U, nicknamed “the weakest hunter of all mankind,” finds himself in a constant struggle for survival. One day, after a brutal encounter in an overpowered dungeon wipes out his party and threatens to end his life, a mysterious System chooses him as its sole player: Jin-U has been granted the rare opportunity to level up his abilities, possibly beyond any known limits. Follow Jin-U’s journey as he takes on ever-stronger enemies, both human and monster, to discover the secrets deep within the dungeons and the ultimate extent of his powers.\n<br><br>\n(Source: Tappytoon)\n<br><br>\n<i>Note: Includes 22 extra chapters.</i>",
        "genres": [
          "Action",
          "Adventure",
          "Fantasy"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 101517,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Jujutsu Kaisen",
          "english": "Jujutsu Kaisen"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx101517-H3TdM3g5ZUe9.jpg"
        },
        "description": "Although Yuji Itadori looks like your average teenager, his immense physical strength is something to behold! Every sports club wants him to join, but Itadori would rather hang out with the school outcasts in the Occult Research Club. One day, the club manages to get their hands on a sealed cursed object. Little do they know the terror they’ll unleash when they break the seal…\n<br><br>\n(Source: VIZ Media)\n<br><br>\n<i>Notes:<br>\n- Ranked 1st in Japan's Bookstore Employees Top Manga of 2018.<br>\n- Nominated for the 25th Annual Tezuka Osamu Cultural Prize in 2021.<br>\n- Nominated for the 65th Shogakukan Manga Award in the Shounen Category in 2019.<br>\n- Includes one extra chapter.</i>",
        "genres": [
          "Action",
          "Drama",
          "Supernatural"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 30002,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Berserk",
          "english": "Berserk"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx30002-Cul4OeN7bYtn.jpg"
        },
        "description": "His name is Guts, the Black Swordsman, a feared warrior spoken of only in whispers. Bearer of a gigantic sword, an iron hand, and the scars of countless battles and tortures, his flesh is also indelibly marked with The Brand, an unholy symbol that draws the forces of darkness to him and dooms him as their sacrifice. But Guts won't take his fate lying down; he'll cut a crimson swath of carnage through the ranks of the damned—and anyone else foolish enough to oppose him! Accompanied by Puck the Elf, more an annoyance than a companion, Guts relentlessly follows a dark, bloodstained path that leads only to death...or vengeance.<br>\n<br>\n(Source: Dark Horse)<br>\n<br>\n<i>Notes:<br>\n- Volumes 1-5 contain the 16 prequel chapters 0A - 0P.<br>\n- <a href=\"https://anilist.co/manga/95821/\">Chapter 83</a> was omitted from Volume 13 due to the author’s request.<br>\n- Volume 14 includes “<a href=\"https://anilist.co/manga/36408/\">Berserk: The Prototype</a>”.<br>\n- Due to the author's passing, starting from Chapter 365, the manga is illustrated by Studio Gaga (Miura's assistants) and supervised by Kouji Mori (a close friend of Miura's).</i>",
        "genres": [
          "Action",
          "Adventure",
          "Drama",
          "Fantasy",
          "Horror",
          "Psychological"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 53390,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "Shingeki no Kyojin",
          "english": "Attack on Titan"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx53390-1RsuABC34P9D.jpg"
        },
        "description": "In this post-apocalyptic sci-fi story, humanity has been devastated by the bizarre, giant humanoids known as the Titans. Little is known about where they came from or why they are bent on consuming mankind. Seemingly unintelligent, they have roamed the world for years, killing everyone they see. For the past century, what's left of man has hidden in a giant, three-walled city. People believe their 50-meter-high walls will protect them from the Titans, but the sudden appearance of an immense Titan is about to change everything.\n<br><br>\n(Source: Kodansha USA)\n<br><br>\n<i>Note: Includes two extra chapters.</i>",
        "genres": [
          "Action",
          "Drama",
          "Fantasy",
          "Mystery"
        ]
      },
      {
        "id": 30013,
        "title": {
          "romaji": "ONE PIECE",
          "english": "One Piece"
        },
        "coverImage": {
          "large": "https://s4.anilist.co/file/anilistcdn/media/manga/cover/medium/bx30013-BeslEMqiPhlk.jpg"
        },
        "description": "As a child, Monkey D. Luffy was inspired to become a pirate by listening to the tales of the buccaneer \"Red-Haired\" Shanks. But his life changed when Luffy accidentally ate the Gum-Gum Devil Fruit and gained the power to stretch like rubber...at the cost of never being able to swim again! Years later, still vowing to become the king of the pirates, Luffy sets out on his adventure...one guy alone in a rowboat, in search of the legendary \"One Piece,\" said to be the greatest treasure in the world...\n<br><br>\n(Source: VIZ Media)",
        "genres": [
